      <back>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>Ossuary has inner ledge on two sides and flat, bulging lid. Height describes that of chest plus that of lid. The name also occurs on ossuaries in its Greek forms Ἐσκίας and Ἐζεκίας, is common in Josephus, and is carried by several Talmudic scholars from the late-first century CE onward.</p>
